FBIS3-31932 "drlat020_g_94009" FBIS-LAT-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 Guatemala Dynamite Deactivated, Grenades Seized PA2801205694 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1826 GMT 28 Jan 94 PA2801205694 Mexico City NOTIMEX Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Guatemala City, 28 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- Police sources reported that the Guatemalan National Police had seized five RPG-7 grenades today in a local restaurant and that a dynamite charge placed at the base of an electricity transmission tower had been deactivated. The National Police Public Relations Department disclosed that the five grenades were hidden in different areas of "Los Antojitos" restaurant which specializes in Mexican food. Four days ago the police also seized 10 rifle grenades in several commercial establishments located throughout Guatemala City. The police report says that a powerful dynamite charge which had been placed at the base of an electricity transmission tower was deactivated this morning. The electricity tower is located in Villanueva colony, at kilometer 13. [passage omitted]
